    {
      "id": "edge-class-library-index",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Library Index",
      "position": {
        "x": -80,
        "y": -170
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 230,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Edge Class Library\n\nCanonical edge-class artifacts live here.\n\n- `task.depends-on`\n- `planning.answers`\n- `graph.implements`\n- `tutorial.edge-class-demo`\n- `graph.entry`\n- `local.content`\n- `home.primary`\n- `home.secondary`\n- `home.context`\n\nPlain edges remain valid without classes. These artifacts exist for relationship semantics that need reusable meaning, legend exposure, and shared render defaults.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
